node.text:
So many amazing memories with Uncle D. Our time in Japan together will always hold a special place in my heart. 
.
Derek Ho was honored today at Pipeline -where he was king.  Hundreds if not over 1000 people gathered for a beautiful ceremony and paddle out to lay his ashes.  By official decree today is officially now Derek K Ho day in Hawaii!! 
.
Always love you Uncle Derek and the entire Ho Ohana. 
.
 #aloha #alohaderekho #derekkhoday #rainbow @freesurfmag @derekho1980 #surfing

node.title: The legendary Derek Ho, Hawaii’s first world champion!!!

Your team is everyone you surround yourself with and soooo many people made this possible !!!! So many people believed in me and Nazare. So many have dedicated their life to seeing this dream become a reality!!! Thank you to everyone who was apart of this. Every positive thought from everyone around the world made this happen!!! THANK YOU!!
.

Without this planet we will all die. It is time we unite for the the greater good of humanity. Together we can make a difference. Every time you spend even a $1 you are either promoting the current single us plastic situation or protesting it. Every time you put food in your mouth you are either supporting local, organic agriculture or you are supporting deforestation, poisoned soil and a plethora of other challenges. Every moment of every day you are making a choice. So if you a celebrating EARTH DAY then make a commitment to make earth day choices every day!!!
.
.
.
#foreverforward #bringyourlife #bringyourkids #getoutside #earthfocus #earthday2021 
.

So wrong it’s right !!!
The 4 o’clock bomb came at 5:00

@matahidrollet paddle or tow hands down the BEST AT CHOOP’S 🙌🙌🙌
Congrats again brother. 
I remember meeting you as a young boy when you were with Raimana on the @apple shoot and he was working with you like a big brother. It was awesome to see your brother @manoa_drollet take you out there and wait nine hours for the wave of the day. Your brother was always the one that got the wave of the day and now you are. 

Matahi Drollet is no stranger to giant Teahupoo. His older brother Manoa (along with Raimana Van Bastolaer) was among the first crew to really charge here over a decade ago; Manoa was also the one towing Matahi yesterday, during one of the biggest swells to hit that bit of reef since Code Red in 2011. Drollet played the patience game, which paid off around 5pm, right before sunset, as the swell peaked and he was whipped in the perfect spot by his brother and took the perfect line through an impossibly heavy, crazy loud, building-sized tube — and straight into surf history. Stay tuned for more coverage. 

🎥 @timmckenna 
@10barrelbrewing

HAPPY BIRTHDAY to my amazing husband Garrett!!! I am sooooo glad he was born and that our two souls collided. It wasn’t the best timing but there was no stopping our love and the collective mission of making the world a better place. This PHOTO was taken during @surfershealing #puertorico !!! That is NOT our child. It is one of the many kids who gets to experience the ocean and surfing through Surfers Healing. The first time we ever laid eyes on each other was at a Surfers Healing event. Surfing and the ocean brought us together. The ocean has given us everything we have and I believe the ocean has made Garrett who he is. HAPPY BIRTHDAY to the most charismatic, loving, caring, thoughtful man!!! You keep life light and fun. So excited to spend the next 50 years with you!!!
.

Mavericks!!!
This was a fun one, 
I remember this day well, @kealiihawaii and I towed for hours. The fog was so thick we had to wait on the beach all morning 
We finally decided to go for it and drive through the harbor in the thick fog hugging the jetty 
We somehow got through to the line up 
It was a miracle, there was a big hole in the sky right around the lineup everywhere else is socked in!
@jamie_mitcho was out among a few of the boys, the Mavericks crew.
Earlier that morning I took @john_john_florence  out for his first look at Mavs
As we pulled up we saw @darrylfleavirostko coming down a bomb, he falls back and does this crazy lay back basically gets munched by the wave and somehow Pops back to his feet and makes it John John sitting on the back of my ski grab me tight and said I got the shivers from that one 
That’s when I quickly rushed back and I got Kealii. 
I remember my goal was to get barreled but this wave as I got to the bottom I was basically rolling up the windows on my heels and I couldn’t bottom turn 
I did the exactly same thing on the next wave every time came up smiling was so fun so many good waves Kealii was killing it surfing with effortless ease.
